            . On the 11th of March, at half-past twelve o'clock, the prisoner came to me and said, my husband, who is a <rs id="t18240407-141-viclabel788" type="occupation">lighterman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240407-141-victim1297 t18240407-141-viclabel788"></join>, had fallen overboard and was almost drowned, and had sent him for some dry things to put on - he was a stranger. I gave him the clothes stated in the indictment, and a crown-piece, as I knew my husband had no money, and told him to give it to my husband to get something to drink before he came home.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. It was not a crown-piece, but two half-crowns - and she gave me a waistcoat, not a jacket.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
            
